        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Hiroya Nozaki",
          "email": "nozaki.hiroya@jp.fujitsu.com",
          "date": "2012-11-02 06:27:45.000000000",
          "tz": 540
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Hiroya Nozaki",
          "email": "nozaki.hiroya@jp.fujitsu.com",
          "date": "2012-11-16 08:23:45.000000000",
          "tz": 540
        },
        "subject": "LU-2258 mount: solve races between evict and umount",
        "message": "LU-2258 mount: solve races between evict and umount\n\nThere are two race conditions between evict and umount.\n\n1) The one race is that obd_export_evict_by_xxx() can touch a\n   lustre hash which has already been finalized but not unregistered yet.\n\n2) The other race is that the class_decref() in\n   lprocfs_wr_evict_client() can call lprocfs_remove() via osc_cleanup()\n   while having _lprocfs_lock already. That's why this case ends up in a\n   deadlock.\n\nThis patch solve these problems with the below solutions.\nFor 1)\n- When evict processes is going on, obd_evict_inprogress will be\n  incremented.\n- class_cleanup() waits until obd_evict_inprogress reaches zero in order\n  for evict processes not to touch the already-finalized-hash.\n- obd_export_evict_by_xxx() see if obd_stopping is set  in order not to\n  touch the already-finalized-hash\n\nFor 2)\n- move class_incref() to just after LPROCFS_EXIT()\n- move class_decref() to just before LPROCFS_ENTRY()\n\nSigned-off-by: Hiroya Nozaki <nozaki.hiroya@jp.fujitsu.com>\nChange-Id: I85a2ed0f59700c7551d16e53b35c45a564c0fe44\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/b1_8"
    }
  },
